textDisplay: Ten does an amazing job dancing here. But I’m over the sexy romance /boy in luv/bad boy concepts for NCT as a whole. It’s obviously an easy grab for teens who will hype up their visuals but some people care about substance too and are a little older like the boys themselves. I also know these men have stories to tell that aren’t rehashings of love lyrics we’ve all heard before. The lyrics are almost annoying in cliches which are fine when they don’t come back to back. At the very least if it was personal and had some of their life story/explored other topics related to their age-I would’ve enjoyed potentially , but the intent is just to show off Ten’s visuals and dancing while capitalizing off the “mature” illusion. And it’s late tbh since his single debut came out a while ago and NCT has kind of stagnated to the point where subgroups like Dream and individuals who work outside the group are bigger than the whole or even NCT 127. To be from SM they’re really not as large as they could be and it’s partially because they never change the content. Hopefully Sm utilizes the talent they have better and explores their range.
textOriginal:
Ten does an amazing job dancing here. But I’m over the sexy romance /boy in luv/bad boy concepts for NCT as a whole. It’s obviously an easy grab for teens who will hype up their visuals but some people care about substance too and are a little older like the boys themselves. I also know these men have stories to tell that aren’t rehashings of love lyrics we’ve all heard before. The lyrics are almost annoying in cliches which are fine when they don’t come back to back. At the very least if it was personal and had some of their life story/explored other topics related to their age-I would’ve enjoyed potentially , but the intent is just to show off Ten’s visuals and dancing while capitalizing off the “mature” illusion. 

And it’s late tbh since his single debut came out a while ago and NCT has kind of stagnated to the point where subgroups like Dream and individuals who work outside the group are bigger than the whole or even NCT 127. To be from SM they’re really not as large as they could be and it’s partially because they never change the content. Hopefully Sm utilizes the talent they have better and explores their range.

textDisplay: There truly aren’t enough words to describe the pride and love I feel for Ten. He has been working so hard this past year, first on PMN and Low Low, then the NCT2021 and his trip to China. His projects there with the biggest being GCD. Coming back to Korea and immediately rehearsing and performing on all kinds of festivals, concerts and also filming the second season of Food Truck Battle. And now this. You can see the time and effort he’s put into this and I truly hope this won’t get unnoticed. Ten’s way of working, his love for music, dance and performing is something so special and admirable. I hope he knows how loved he is and how incredibly proud we are of him. He deserves all the love and recognition, let’s continue to give him that and more and support him every day. ❤

He has been working so hard this past year, first on PMN and Low Low, then the NCT2021 and his trip to China. His projects there with the biggest being GCD. Coming back to Korea and immediately rehearsing and performing on all kinds of festivals, concerts and also filming the second season of Food Truck Battle. And now this. You can see the time and effort he’s put into this and I truly hope this won’t get unnoticed. Ten’s way of working, his love for music, dance and performing is something so special and admirable. I hope he knows how loved he is and how incredibly proud we are of him. He deserves all the love and recognition, let’s continue to give him that and more and support him every day. ❤
